            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Ralph G. Lindstrom, born in Illinois in 1891, was a prominent attorney in Los Angeles. A frequent contributor to the <emph render="italic">Christian Science Monitor</emph>, he was also a frequent speaker on Lincoln topics. President of the Lincoln Fellowship of Southern California and of the Lincoln Sesquicentennial Association of California, he wrote <emph render="italic">Lincoln Finds God</emph> (1958).</p>
                                 <p>This collection includes typescripts of a number of papers that Lindstrom delivered, mostly on Lincoln. It also includes a portfolio of reviews of <emph render="italic">Lincoln Finds God</emph>, pictures of Lindstrom&#039;s appearance on CBS when the book was published, and excerpts of letters which he received when the book was serialized in the <emph render="italic">Christian Science Monitor</emph>. Lindstrom&#039;s book went through many drafts between 1952 and 1961, much of which was set aside. Lindstrom planned to revise this material for another book, &quot;Lincoln and &#039;Man&#039;s Vast Future,&#039;&quot; a sample of which is retained in this collection.</p>
                                 <p>The collection was acquired from Chuck Hand of Paris, Ill.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


